As TUSCON spoke the expression on his face darkened as he crossed his
arms over his chest, his optics smoldering with repressed anger and
heat. There was no flinching from RODIMUS, no stepping back and most
certainly no fear.

&quot;What you did?&quot; RODIMUS said in low tones that would not carry over to
the Predacons, but his words were fierc, obviously his own temper
finally about to explode as well. The look on his face was one of
disbelief.

&quot;You&#39;re going to try holding that over my head?&quot; There was a shake of
his head. &quot;I had to live with these *Predacons*&quot; RODIMUS spit out the
word &#39;Predacon&#39; like a curse. &quot;And they changed me into a monster!
They captured my wife and had me hold her while they tried to change
her! I was about to loose my family because of them and you want me to
work with them now, after all that?&quot; The incredulousness of it all was
in every word he spoke.

If TUSCON thought RODIMUS was a shrinking wall flower and would cave
in he was mistaken.

RODIMUS breathed in deep, it had been a while since his own temper had
come out, and yet once it did, it felt good - he had spent so much
time having to reign it in.

&quot;We have *both* sacrificed to save others many times&quot; RODIMUS said in
a hard whisper. &quot;And for you to try to hold that over my head . . . to
try and guilt me into doing something like that . . . that is beneath
all of us and I thought you as well.&quot;

Turning away from TUSCON he started to stalk towards the Dinosaurs
RODIMUS&#39; whole frame rigid, it would be some time for him to calm down
as well. &quot;We will talk about this later Tuscon, for now we have to
finish what you have started.&quot;

At the same time LEO PRIME&#39;s voice came back over the comlink, &quot;I will
send the Fuzors to you. They should be there in a couple of hours.&quot;
There was a pause from LEO, &quot;But I need to know what you&#39;re trying to
do. Working with the Predacons is a dangerous business.&quot;

